Package: textsampler
Type: Package
Title: Text sampling in R
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2019-09-10
Authors@R: c(person("Nicolas", "Proellochs", email="nicolas.proellochs@wi.jlug.de",
                    role=c("aut", "cre")))
Maintainer: Nicolas Proellochs <nicolas.proellochs@wi.jlug.de>
Description: The textsampler R-Package samples texts from a predefined text source. This implementation uses tidy data principles 
        and works seamlessly with existing text mining packages such as tm, tidytext, and rvest. 
        In addition, it supplies multiple built-in text datasets for hassle-free sampling of words, sentences, and texts.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Depends: R (>= 3.2.0)
Imports:
    tidytext,
    dplyr,
    magrittr,
    tibble,
    tm,
    textclean,
    stringr
Suggests:
    testthat,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
LazyData: TRUE
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
VignetteBuilder: knitr
